Data Collection

(Was done on the Tufts High Performance Cluster w/ 16 cores and 200 GB of memory)
- Weather Data
    - Use the open-mateo historical weather API
        - Select parameters for date range (1/1/2025 - 12/31/2025), location (Boston), hourly weather variables (precipitation), and use the resulting api link

- Train Arrival Data
  - Use the MBTA Blue Book Open Data for MBTA Rapid Transit Travel Times 2025 (https://mbta-massdot.opendata.arcgis.com/datasets/5f71a5c035fc4a4dad1b7fa73ba27ef8/about)
  - For our project, you only needed to use the LRT travel times, but trains.ipynb uses all train data

- Trains.ipynb (Part 1)
 -  Use this Jupyter notebook to merge the information on train arrival time with weather data, and put all this information into a parquet file

- theBigUnzip.ipynb
  - Get the links to zip files of the archive data from https://cdn.mbta.com/archive/archived_feeds.txt (would use equivalent schedule data if you were to analyze some other train system)
  - 




